<span id="freeTextContainer4594688376731188426">Life is too short to endure bad fiction.<br/><br/>The story started out interesting enough, with the characters literally falling out of the sky. It took me a awhile to get into the story, but I finally did. The problem was that every time you managed to get a hold of the basic underlying narrative it would evaporate and be replaced by a nonsensical dream sequence. The transitions between the two realities was so seamless that you frequently find yourself lost. Add all of that to the fact that you are try</span>
  <span id="freeText4594688376731188426" style="display:none">Life is too short to endure bad fiction.<br /><br />The story started out interesting enough, with the characters literally falling out of the sky. It took me a awhile to get into the story, but I finally did. The problem was that every time you managed to get a hold of the basic underlying narrative it would evaporate and be replaced by a nonsensical dream sequence. The transitions between the two realities was so seamless that you frequently find yourself lost. Add all of that to the fact that you are trying to juggle the names of very foreign persons and places and it gets even worse.<br /><br />I think that, perhaps, to approach this book and appreciate it you have to have a working knowledge of the Koran and Persian Mythology.<br /><br />I also think that the book would have never been have read by as many people as it has been were it not for the controversy surrounding it.</span>
